<div>
  <h1 class="mt-4 mt-lg-5">About Me</h1>
  <hr>
</div>

<div class="custom-wrapper bg-tranparent">

  <div class="mb-4">
    <div class="row gy-3">
      <div class="col-md-5 text-center">
        <%= image_tag "profile.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "profile image", width: 350, height: 350 %>
      </div>
    
      <div class="col-md-7 text-start">
        <p class="lead">I am a Full-Stack Developer with a strong focus on Ruby on Rails and a passion for crafting scalable, high-performance web applications.</p>
    
        <p class="lead">With experience across full-stack software development, I specialize in Ruby and the Ruby on Rails framework, along with expertise in JavaScript, jQuery, PHP, and WordPress development.</p>
    
        <p class="lead">My technical stack also includes RSpec for testing, frontend frameworks like Tailwind, Bootstrap, and Foundation, and database management with PostgreSQL and MySQL. I also work with AWS services such as S3 for cloud storage and IAM for secure access management. Additionally, I have a well-rounded understanding of Linux administration, ensuring smooth deployment and maintenance of applications.</p>
    
        <p class="lead">I take a collaborative and transparent approach to development, prioritizing clear communication and well-structured design patterns. When working on a project, I not only build applications to meet client specifications but also provide regular updates to ensure alignment with their vision.</p>
    
      </div>
    </div>
    
  </div>

  <div>
    
    <h1>Technical Skills</h1>

    <hr>
   
    <div class="row">
      <% @skills.each_slice((@skills.size / 2.0).ceil) do |skills_column| %>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <% skills_column.each do |skill| %>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <h4 class="mb-0 text-start"><%= skill.title %></h4>
              <div class="progress w-75">
                <div
                  class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped progress-bar-bg"
                  role="progressbar"
                  aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_utilized %>"
                  aria-valuemin="0"
                  aria-valuemax="100"
                  style="width: <%= skill.percent_utilized %>%"
                >
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>